GN-Geoportal is a portal for searching and displaying spatial metadata records in a GeoNetwork catalog (http://geonetwork-opensource.org/).  GN-Geoportal is written in Ruby and employs the Sinatra DSL.

Required gems: nokogiri, haml

To update CSS with Sass:
gem sources --add http://gems.github.com/
sudo gem install chriseppstein-compass
Make changes to src/*.sass then
cd config
compass -u

To run the application at http://localhost:4567 via WEBrick, type
ruby app.rb

A config.ru file is also included for Rack-based deployment.

By Joe Gilbert (joe.gilbert@gmail.com).